# AWS EKS Migration - Task Checklist

## Phase 1: Preparation
- [ ] Review current infrastructure
- [ ] Install/verify AWS CLI and eksctl
- [ ] Create EKS migration plan
- [ ] Backup current configurations

## Phase 2: Infrastructure Cleanup
- [ ] Document current K8s resources
- [ ] Terminate K8s master server
- [ ] Terminate K8s worker server
- [ ] Update Terraform to remove K8s instances

## Phase 3: EKS Cluster Setup
- [ ] Install eksctl and kubectl
- [ ] Create EKS cluster with eksctl
- [ ] Verify cluster connectivity
- [ ] Configure kubectl context

## Phase 4: Application Deployment
- [ ] Apply Kubernetes manifests to EKS
- [ ] Deploy monitoring stack
- [ ] Verify pod health
- [ ] Test application endpoints

## Phase 5: Webhook Integration
- [ ] Update webhook server configuration
- [ ] Configure RBAC for webhook
- [ ] Test webhook connectivity
- [ ] Configure Docker Hub webhooks

## Phase 6: Verification
- [ ] Verify all services running
- [ ] Test end-to-end functionality
- [ ] Monitor logs and metrics
